parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power tailgate control module can cause the tailgate to malfunction, leading to safety concerns, such as the tailgate opening unexpectedly while driving, or not opening at all, which can be a hazard for occupants or other motorists.
symptoms: The tailgate does not open or close properly
the tailgate opens slowly or not at all
error messages appear on the dashboard
the tailgate makes a beeping sound
and the battery drains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, such as the brake system, lane keeping assist, adaptive cruise control, and collision mitigation system, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard
warning lights illuminate
the vehicle experiences sudden braking incidents
the electrical system requires replacement
and the vehicle's acceleration is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body seam seal can cause water to enter the vehicle, leading to corrosion of electrical components, such as the power tailgate control module, which can cause safety concerns.
symptoms: Water enters the vehicle
the power tailgate control module is corroded
and the tailgate malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the brake system warning light illuminates
and the vehicle experiences sudden braking incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic transmission shifting can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lurch forward, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
hesitates
or lurches forward
causing unexpected acceleration or deceleration. The vehicle may also experience sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or neutralizing can cause the vehicle to lose power or acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips or neutralizes
causing the vehicle to lose power or acceleration. The vehicle may also experience sudden loss of speed or unexpected downshifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
causing sudden surges of power or speed. The vehicle may also experience sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or no acceleration can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when the accelerator pedal is pressed. The vehicle may also experience sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission error codes and warnings can indicate a problem with the transmission, which can lead to accidents or loss of control if not addressed.
symptoms: The vehicle displays transmission error codes or warnings on the dashboard
indicating a problem with the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning sliding doors can cause inconvenience, safety concerns, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The door fails to close or opens unexpectedly
sometimes trapping objects or body parts
and may require manual closure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation in acceleration can lead to accidents, especially when merging into traffic or making turns.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate immediately when the pedal is pressed
sometimes resulting in sudden acceleration or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera can increase the risk of accidents, especially when reversing.
symptoms: The camera displays a black screen or fails to function
making it difficult to see obstacles behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress can cause electrical failures, leading to safety concerns and potential accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle
causing damage to electrical components
such as the control module or tailgate motor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof/moonroof can cause injuries and accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof/moonroof shatters or explodes without warning
sometimes causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete recalls in a timely manner can leave vehicles with safety defects on the road, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Dealerships are unable to complete recalls due to parts availability issues
leaving customers frustrated and concerned about their vehicle's safety.
